cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.AI, cs.CL

The paper discusses the impact of margin distribution optimisation on generalisation in deep architectures, which is a topic closely related to machine learning and neural networks. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also proposes a new loss function for deep learning models, which falls under the category of optimization algorithms, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely sub-category as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its proposed method on image datasets, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.CL (Computation and Language).
